{{Reflist}}

[[Category:Physical objects]]


{{science-stub}}

'''Microenvironment'''  in biology is defined as the normal cells, molecules, and blood vessels that surround and feed a particular cellular area. The microenvironment in a [[tumor]] is different from that of a healthy organ; the microenvironment can affect how the tumor grows and spreads.<ref>[https://www.cancer.gov/publications/dictionaries/cancer-terms/def/791175 Microenvironment] NCI Dictionary, undated, retrieved 7 December 2017</ref>
The term originated in the [[oncology]] literature in 1975<ref>Preisler HD, Bjornsson S, Mori M, Barcos M.Granulocyte differentiation by Friend leukemia cells.Cell Differ. 1975 Dec;4(5):273-83.</ref> and has been used with increasing frequency in the biomedical literature since the 2000´s.<ref>[https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed Pubmed search on tumor microenvironment] retrieved 7 December 2017</ref> 
