{{Infobox award | name = VASVIK Industrial Research Award | image = | alt = | description = Research in [[interdisciplinarity|science]] in [[India]] | presenter = Vividhlaxi Audyogik Samshodhan Vikas Kendra | location = Patel Vanika, [[Mumbai]], India | year = 1976 | website = [http://www.vasvik.org/index.html VASVIK Award website] }}
'''VASVIK Industrial Research Award''' is an Indian award, instituted to recognize and promote excellence in industrial research in the areas of science and technology.<ref name="Narendra Modi">{{cite web | url=http://www.narendramodi.in/chief-minister-presents-vasvik-awards-to-25-scientists-honours-mgk-menon/ | title=Narendra Modi | publisher=Narendra Modi | date=2011 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="INT">{{cite web | url=http://www.indiannewsandtimes.com/2013/12/17/vasvik-research-awards-given-aim-promoting-industrial-research-science-technology-india/ | title=INT | publisher=INT | date=22 December 2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref> The award is given annually to individuals or groups and carries a citation and a cash prize of {{INR}} 100,000.<ref name="INT" /><ref name="Award home">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/aboutus.html | title=Award home | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref>
==Profile== VASVIK awards have been instituted by Vividhlaxi Audyogik Samshodhan Vikas Kendra (VASVIK),<ref name="Narendra Modi" /> a non profit making [[non governmental organization]] established in 1974 by the Mumbai based business family of Patels,<ref name="INT" /><ref name="PEG">{{cite web | url=http://www.epltube.com/ | title=PEG | publisher=PEG | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref> headed by Mohan Patel, an ex Sheriff of Mumbai, who is credited with the development of the first ophthalmic nozzle pure aluminum tube.<ref name="Mohan Patel">{{cite web | url=http://www.icgeb.trieste.it/tl_files/News/25%20awarded%20for%20industrial%20research%20-%20Times%20Of%20India.pdf | title=Mohan Patel | publisher=Mohan Patel | date=2011 | accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref> The awards are annual in cycle and have been instituted with a view to promote industry based research in India in the fields of science and technology. Nine categories have been identified for the awards and individuals and groups are eligible for the awards, except one, which is reserved for women scientists.<ref name="INT" /> The awardees are selected by a Board of Advisors nominated by the organization. The awards honour innovation in design and production techniques which foster economic growth of the country by way of import substitution, reduction of manufacturing costs and foreign exchange saving.<ref name="About us">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/aboutus.html | title=About us | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref>
==Categories== The awards are distributed in nine categories of which 8 are open categories and ''Chandaben Mohanbhai Patel Industrial Research Award'' is extended to women scientists only.<ref name="Categories">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/award_catagories.html | title=Categories | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref> {{Div col}} * Agricultural Sciences and Technology<ref name="Agriculture">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/agricultural_sciences%20_&_technology.html | title=Agriculture | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="DNA India">{{cite web | url=http://www.dnaindia.com/pune/report-vasvik-research-award-for-ncl-scientist-1881705 | title=DNA India | publisher=DNA India | date=2013 | accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref> * Biological Sciences and Technology<ref name="Biology">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/biological_sciences_&_technology.html | title=Biology | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Mohan Patel" /><ref name="ICT Mumbai">{{cite web | url=http://www.ictmumbai.edu.in/newsFiles%5CVASAVIK%20%20Foundation%20Award.docx | title=ICT Mumbai | publisher=ICT Mumbai | date=2014 | accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref> * Chemical Sciences and Technology<ref name="Chemistry">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/chemical_sciences_&_technology.html | title=Chemistry | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Mohan Patel" /><ref name="ICT Mumbai" /> * Electrical and Electronic Sciences and Technology<ref name="Electrical">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/Electrical_&_Electronic_Sciences_&_Technology.html | title=Electrical | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Mohan Patel" /> * Environmental Sciences and Technology<ref name="Environment">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/Environmental_Sciences_&_Technology.html | title=Environment | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Mohan Patel" /><ref name="IITB">{{cite web | url=http://www.iitb.ac.in/en/award/vasvik-award-2014-0 | title=IITB | publisher=IITB | date=2014 | accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref> * Mechanical and Structural Sciences and Technology<ref name="Mechanical">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/Mechanical_&_Structural_Sciences_&_Technology.html | title=Mechanical | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Mohan Patel" /><ref name="The Hindu">{{cite web | url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-andhrapradesh/vasvik-award-for-bhujanga-rao/article2519766.ece | title=The Hindu | publisher=The Hindu | date=2011 | accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref> * Information and Communication Technology<ref name="IT">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/Information_&_Communication_Technology.html | title=IT | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Cdac">{{cite web | url=http://cdac.in/index.aspx?id=pk_itn_spot891 | title=Cdac | publisher=Cdac | date=2012 | accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref> * Materials Sciences and Technology<ref name="Material">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/Materials_Sciences_&_Technology.html | title=Material | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Mohan Patel" /> * Chandaben Mohanbhai Patel Industrial Research Award for Women Scientists<ref name="Chandaben">{{cite web | url=http://www.vasvik.org/Women's_Award.html | title=Chandaben | publisher=Vasvik | date=2014 | accessdate=January 4, 2015}}</ref><ref name="Newswala">{{cite web | url=http://www.newswala.com/Hyderabad-News/VASVIK-Award-for-CSIR-IICT-Director-Dr.-M.-Lakshmi-Kantam-53417.html | title=Newswala | publisher=Newswala | date=2011 | accessdate=January 5, 2015}}</ref><ref name="ICT Mumbai" /> {{div col end}}
